# THE EXECUTION RULES

## 1. MEAL PREP (Sunday)
**Spend 90 minutes:**
- Cook all grains (oats, rice, quinoa) for the week
- Grill 800g chicken breast
- Boil 18 eggs (for egg whites throughout week)
- Chop vegetables for 3 days
- Portion everything in containers

**This removes 90% of daily decisions.**

## 2. MEASURING (First 2 weeks - strict)
**Weigh these religiously:**
- All proteins (raw or cooked, be consistent)
- All grains/carbs (cooked weight)
- All fats (this is critical - no eyeballing oils/nuts)
- Use a food scale, not volume measurements

**After 2 weeks, you can eyeball portions because you've calibrated.**

## 3. NO SUBSTITUTIONS (First 4 weeks)
**Don't get creative:**
- Eat exactly what's written
- Rotate the 2 options per meal type
- Don't add "just a little" extra anything

**Boring = results.**

## 4. TRACKING
**Daily (first 2 weeks):**
- Weight (same time, after bathroom, before eating)
- Waist measurement (weekly, Sunday morning)

**Weekly average weight trend matters, not daily fluctuations.**

## 5. ADJUSTMENTS (After week 3)

**IF losing 0.5-1kg/week:** ✅ Continue exactly as is

**IF not losing after 3 weeks:** 
- Cut 30g carbs from cardio/rest days (remove toast or reduce rice)
- DON'T add more cardio yet

**IF losing >1.5kg/week:**
- Add 30g carbs to post-workout meals
- Maintain protein

